SIMPLE: blinker
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Blinker
<hw>Blink"er</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who, or that which, blinks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A blinder for horses; a flap of leather on a horse's
bridle to prevent him from seeing objects as his side hence, whatever
obstructs sight or discernment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nor bigots who but one way see,⟦br⟧
through <qex>blinkers</qex> of authority.</q> <rj><qau>M.
Green.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <pos>pl.</pos> <def>A kind of goggles, used to protect
the eyes form glare, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blink-eyed</ent>⟦br⟧
